<hl>
<seg id=1> Sino-Foreign Cooperations in Building Materials Industry Develop Fast. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Beijing. March 19. (Reporter Lijianmin) China's building materials industry takes strengthening co-operations with foreign countries as a key measure for quickening development. Domain of making use of foreign funds has been quickly widened. For the time being, the total foreign funds attracted by the whole industry has reached $5 billion. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> A responsible official from the State Bureau of Building Materials Industry revealed today that at present a great number of cement projects, such as Tongling in Anhui and Xiangxiang in Hunan, undertaken by China's building materials industry of China with loans from Bank of World and Bank of Asia have been put into production one after another. </seg>
<seg id=4> The domain of foreign investment is now rapidly developing into the aspects of novel building materials, high and new technology and deep-going processing. </seg>
<seg id=5> The technical innovation program of high-grade hygiene porcelain set up with US$0.1 billion of exporting credit loan on favorable terms from Italy is now making active progress in Shaanxi, Shandong, Guangdong, Jilin, Hunan and so on. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Recently, the building materials industry of China has signed bilateral cooperation agreements with the governments of Netherlands, Germany, Thailand, Greece, Australia, Japan, France, Denmark, etc. as well as multi-national corporations. And its foreign partners have increased considerably. </seg>
<seg id=7> last year, China earned US$2.1 billion of net foreign exchange profits in building materials exporting. It exported 12 million tons of cement, increasing by 46%over last year and set a best record in history. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Besides, China has introduced from abroad an assembly line of initial distribution & kiln dissolution, and set up such modern and large-scale cement enterprises as Jidong, Ningbo, Huaihai, Lirzhou, etc., newly increasing cement production capacity of 22 million tons per year. </seg>
</p>
